1
00:00:00,626 --> 00:00:01,919
♪

2
00:00:01,919 --> 00:00:04,421
Do you have what it
takes to Buddyfight?

3
00:00:04,421 --> 00:00:05,631
Choose your favorite world

4
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:06,798
and use special cards

5
00:00:06,798 --> 00:00:10,093
to summon its powerful
monsters into reality.

6
00:00:10,093 --> 00:00:11,512
Challenge other fighters

7
00:00:11,512 --> 00:00:13,430
and Buddy Call
your toughest ally

8
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:15,349
to fight by your side.

9
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:17,351
Get ready to raise the flag!

10
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:20,145
♪

11
00:00:20,145 --> 00:00:22,314
Demon Sommelier, Zagan!

12
00:00:22,314 --> 00:00:26,318
‐Yo, yo, yo.
‐Fallen Angel of Rage, Beleth.

13
00:00:26,318 --> 00:00:29,863
Yo, yo, yo, lemme
hit 'em this time, yo!

14
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:35,118
And my favorite homeboy and
buddy, Demon Lord, Asmodai!

15
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:36,495
In da house!

16
00:00:36,495 --> 00:00:38,539
I have something for you.

17
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:40,499
This time, I won't miss.

18
00:00:40,499 --> 00:00:42,251
(yelling)

19
00:00:42,251 --> 00:00:44,878
♪

20
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:46,838
Here's the finish!

21
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:48,840
You haven't seen
the last of me.

22
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,342
(grunts)

23
00:00:50,342 --> 00:00:52,636
♪

24
00:00:52,636 --> 00:00:56,056
(cheering)

25
00:00:56,056 --> 00:02:24,394
♪

26
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:31,652
The second game
of the final round

27
00:02:31,652 --> 00:02:32,903
is about to begin.

28
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:35,280
But first, after all the
excitement in the last game,

29
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,282
we thought everyone could
use a brief intermission.

30
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:39,493
This would be a perfect time
to visit the concession stand

31
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:41,161
and fill up on some
delicious snacks

32
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:43,914
and check out the fabulous
Buddyfight souvenirs.

33
00:02:45,082 --> 00:02:46,917
Although the suspected
criminal Nobari

34
00:02:46,917 --> 00:02:48,251
was in charge of
the Buddy Police

35
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:49,628
for only a short time,

36
00:02:49,628 --> 00:02:52,464
the damage he's
caused is enormous.

37
00:02:52,464 --> 00:02:53,799
For some perplexing reason,

38
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:55,133
he destroyed most of our files,

39
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,469
which included vital
intel on known offenders

40
00:02:57,469 --> 00:03:00,055
and details on
ongoing investigations.

41
00:03:00,055 --> 00:03:02,516
Because of this, finding and
arresting criminal fighters

42
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:06,144
will prove to be incredibly
difficult for our department.

43
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:08,188
(barrage of questions)

44
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:10,273
Hold on, everyone
please calm down.

45
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:11,650
One question at a time.

46
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:13,527
‐Okay, that's enough.
‐Huh?

47
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:15,028
Police Commissioner Kisaragi.

48
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:16,488
Due to recent events,

49
00:03:16,488 --> 00:03:19,241
our forces will now be
working with the Buddy Police.

50
00:03:19,241 --> 00:03:21,618
We plan to coordinate our
resources in a joint effort

51
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:25,247
to focus our dual energies
on one common goal:

52
00:03:25,247 --> 00:03:28,083
arresting criminal fighters.

53
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:29,543
Hmph, I'm being
pursued by the police,

54
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:31,711
and as luck would have it,
I'm about to go and fight

55
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:33,338
the son of the
police commissioner

56
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:35,507
in front of the whole world.

57
00:03:35,507 --> 00:03:36,925
Well, I guess now
that the Buddy Police

58
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:38,343
are no longer corrupt,

59
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:41,179
you can go running back
home to your little friends.

60
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:43,348
Even if the Buddy Police
are back to normal,

61
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:44,349
this isn't the end.

62
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:47,519
There are still people
out there causing harm.

63
00:03:47,519 --> 00:03:49,354
We need to re‐imagine things

64
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:51,815
so we can free the
world of injustice.

65
00:03:51,815 --> 00:03:55,819
You're starting to sound
more like Kyoya every day.

66
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:57,696
As his friend,
I've sworn to support him

67
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:59,197
no matter what happens.

68
00:03:59,197 --> 00:04:01,450
Tell me, are you
prepared to do the same?

69
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:04,953
I knew what I was getting into.

70
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:07,038
And I won't turn back now.

71
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:10,041
(door slides open)

72
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:12,961
(footsteps)

73
00:04:12,961 --> 00:04:15,422
Ah, there you are, my friend.

74
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:18,091
We have something to discuss.

75
00:04:24,306 --> 00:04:26,600
I came to stress the
importance of your fight

76
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,893
in the second game.

77
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:29,227
You must win at any cost.

78
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:31,062
You really didn't need
to waste your time

79
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:32,981
coming down here, Kyoya.

80
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:36,568
It's me you're talking to,
there's no way that I can lose.

81
00:04:36,568 --> 00:04:38,904
Well, if you do, then
I'm afraid it will mean

82
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:40,906
the end of our friendship.

83
00:04:40,906 --> 00:04:42,824
(exclaims)

84
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:44,075
Hm.

85
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:46,745
That's just a little joke.

86
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:48,163
As for you,

87
00:04:48,163 --> 00:04:49,706
there are a few things
we need to go over

88
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,583
before your big finale.

89
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:54,961
If his plan actually succeeds,

90
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:58,381
thousands of people
will be affected.

91
00:04:58,381 --> 00:05:02,344
But I guess what happens to
them is none of my business.

92
00:05:02,344 --> 00:05:04,971
♪

93
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:06,223
Scissors!

94
00:05:06,223 --> 00:05:07,641
Yes!

95
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:08,600
(explosion)

96
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,811
‐I keep losing!
‐(evil cackle)

97
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:12,604
Drum Dungeon Blade.

98
00:05:12,604 --> 00:05:14,105
(yells)

99
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,732
Now it's time for
the grand finale.

100
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:19,444
I cast Battle Aura Circle!

101
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,905
I got a surprise for you.

102
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:24,282
(maniacal laughter)

103
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:26,201
That guy's gonna win it for us?

104
00:05:26,201 --> 00:05:28,620
Hey, if that pathetic
monster beats you,

105
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:31,706
you'll have to find a new Buddy.

106
00:05:31,706 --> 00:05:32,916
(chuckling)

107
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:34,793
I'm just kiddin'.

108
00:05:34,793 --> 00:05:36,419
(sighs, chuckles)

109
00:05:37,921 --> 00:05:39,256
Then again...

110
00:05:39,256 --> 00:05:41,716
♪

111
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:45,095
Something tells me that
Rouga's having second thoughts.

112
00:05:45,095 --> 00:05:47,013
Buddyfights have
been known to cause

113
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:49,224
great changes in people.

114
00:05:49,224 --> 00:05:51,518
Even you were not
entirely immune to it,

115
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:55,730
as demonstrated by your
frustration in your last match.

116
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:59,192
I never did like the old grouch.

117
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:02,279
If you ask me, we're
better off without him.

118
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:04,406
Well, hello, handsome!

119
00:06:04,406 --> 00:06:05,824
(chuckles)

120
00:06:05,824 --> 00:06:09,119
I guess I'll have
to deal with 'im.

121
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:20,046
♪

122
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:24,009
No, I have an important
fight ahead of me.

123
00:06:24,009 --> 00:06:28,013
I must clear my head
of all distractions.

124
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:29,389
What do we have here?

125
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:30,849
Okay, don't move.

126
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:32,726
On the count of three,
we'll sneak up behind him

127
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:35,770
and scare the pants
offa him, real old school!

128
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,564
No, let him prepare
for his fight.

129
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:40,191
We really need him
to win this one.

130
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:42,110
And let's hope that I do.

131
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:44,529
The thing is, with
that Dark Core of his,

132
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:47,908
Tasuku will be even more
powerful than he used to be.

133
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:49,993
‐I guess so.
‐You've seen what can happen

134
00:06:49,993 --> 00:06:51,828
when they make those
cards into reality.

135
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:54,706
You're right, scaring him
wouldn't have been a good idea.

136
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:56,583
I know you're worried
about the team,

137
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,376
but I think if you
stick to your strengths,

138
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:00,378
you've got a great
chance of winning!

139
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:02,297
Relax, man, you're awesome.

140
00:07:02,297 --> 00:07:04,549
Just be yourself and
do what comes naturally.

141
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:05,675
Uh‐huh.

142
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:06,843
And remember.

143
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:08,720
Us Buds gotta stick together.

144
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,222
Now, lets go beat
those Disaster guys.

145
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:12,390
Hm.

146
00:07:13,642 --> 00:07:16,394
Thanks, Gao,
I really needed that.

147
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:19,439
You know, you just helped me
to realize something important.

148
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,733
‐You're a good friend.
‐I am?

149
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:22,776
Now that's settled.

150
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:24,653
Can we go have our
pre‐fight feast?

151
00:07:24,653 --> 00:07:25,987
There you are, Z.

152
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:27,906
We have a big problem.

153
00:07:27,906 --> 00:07:29,699
What do you mean,
what's happening now?

154
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:33,745
Father's here?

155
00:07:33,745 --> 00:07:36,081
Zanya, we need to talk.

156
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:39,501
It's come to my attention that
your opponent in the final

157
00:07:39,501 --> 00:07:41,378
is a criminal fighter.

158
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:43,713
I know, I think he goes by Wolf.

159
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:45,590
I figured you knew.

160
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:47,926
How come you don't
ever tell me anything?

161
00:07:47,926 --> 00:07:50,387
So are you planning
to arrest him, Father?

162
00:07:50,387 --> 00:07:51,763
That's what I'd like to do.

163
00:07:51,763 --> 00:07:55,100
But because the Buddy Police
lost their evidence against him,

164
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,893
he can walk free.

165
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:59,104
Not for long,
if I can help it.

166
00:07:59,104 --> 00:08:01,940
I'm conducting my own
inquiry into this Wolf.

167
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:05,610
I'm here for a
preliminary investigation.

168
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:08,029
As you know, I was once
a Buddyfighter myself.

169
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:09,322
By watching him fight,

170
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:12,951
I hope to learn more
about his true character.

171
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:15,412
I think I might be able
to help you with that.

172
00:08:15,412 --> 00:08:17,205
♪

173
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:19,457
‐So what do you want?
‐I want you to make me

174
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:20,959
a promise.

175
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:22,085
What would that be?

176
00:08:22,085 --> 00:08:23,920
Promise me that if I win,

177
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,171
you'll go to the police

178
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:28,967
and own up to all of the many
crimes you've committed as Wolf.

179
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:31,052
And if I refuse?

180
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:32,679
Welcome back to the Gaen Cup.

181
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:35,515
The second game of the final
round is about to begin.

182
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:38,893
Representing Team Purgatory
is Rouga Aragami.

183
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,228
(snarling)

184
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:41,688
And from Team Balle du Soleil,

185
00:08:41,688 --> 00:08:44,315
Zanya Kisaragi is
taking to the stage.

186
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:46,484
FYI, this showdown is
between two heavyweights

187
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,819
from Aibo Academy,

188
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:49,821
the former top‐ranked
eighth‐grade fighter

189
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:53,241
and the top‐ranked fighter from
the elementary school division.

190
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:56,119
We are in for a treat, folks.

191
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:59,831
Mr. Gaen sure is amazing
at making match‐ups.

192
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:02,333
The power of the Ace
will destroy you.

193
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:06,171
Dark Luminize, Ace Defeat!

194
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:08,798
(growl)

195
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:10,341
Secret and silent,

196
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,260
but you still hear the sound...

197
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,511
of my mighty sword.

198
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:16,848
Luminize, Kisaragi
needs Arms Type 2!

199
00:09:16,848 --> 00:09:19,350
Come on, let's make some
noise for our contenders.

200
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:22,562
Buddyfight!

201
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,064
(cheering)

202
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:25,857
It's time to raise the flag.

203
00:09:25,857 --> 00:09:27,609
I fight for Danger World.

204
00:09:27,609 --> 00:09:29,527
(growling)

205
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:31,780
I fight for Katana World.

206
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:35,575
♪

207
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,786
The first move goes to Rouga.

208
00:09:37,786 --> 00:09:39,329
Charge and draw.

209
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:41,706
I pay one gauge and equip.

210
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:44,292
Explosive Axe,
Ricdeau Demon Slay.

211
00:09:44,292 --> 00:09:46,669
And I'll use a Set Spell
final battle skill,

212
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:48,463
MAJI Demon Slay.

213
00:09:48,463 --> 00:09:50,715
Right on cue,
Rouga's secret weapon.

214
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:52,884
It's a strategic play
that forces both players

215
00:09:52,884 --> 00:09:54,594
into direct combat.

216
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:57,055
I figured he'd be going
for the same tactic he used

217
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:59,641
‐when he beat Jin.
‐Really, why's that?

218
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:01,059
He uses Katana World.

219
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:04,145
It's extremely weak in
a direct combat situation.

220
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:06,439
So Zanya's at
a major disadvantage.

221
00:10:06,439 --> 00:10:07,607
Not really.

222
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,609
Since he found out ahead of
time who he'd be fighting,

223
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:11,861
I'm sure Zanya made all
the necessary adjustments

224
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:14,280
when he was prepping for today.

225
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,200
(yelling)

226
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,203
I cast Art of Body Replacement.

227
00:10:20,203 --> 00:10:23,248
♪

228
00:10:23,248 --> 00:10:24,707
End of move.

229
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:26,251
Zanya used a
specialty of his own

230
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:27,919
to come out of
this turn unscathed,

231
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:29,963
with no damage at all.

232
00:10:29,963 --> 00:10:31,089
(grimace)

233
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:33,550
I cast Clear Serenity.

234
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:35,593
♪

235
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:38,763
I call Electron Ninja,
Shiden to the right.

236
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:40,723
And I use Shiden's ability,

237
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:43,935
cyberanalyze to draw two cards.

238
00:10:43,935 --> 00:10:47,939
I call Acceleration Ninja,
Hayate to the left.

239
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:52,193
And I equip by
Heavenly Swords Onimaru.

240
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:54,112
I didn't see this one coming.

241
00:10:54,112 --> 00:10:55,363
Zanya's equipped an item.

242
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:57,866
He's leaving his center open
to prepare for a direct

243
00:10:57,866 --> 00:10:59,951
three‐way attack against Rouga.

244
00:10:59,951 --> 00:11:01,119
Was that a happy accident,

245
00:11:01,119 --> 00:11:03,288
or does he actually know
what he's doing out there?

246
00:11:03,288 --> 00:11:05,957
I do power plays better
than the rest of 'em.

247
00:11:05,957 --> 00:11:07,041
We'll see.

248
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,460
You should know that
justice is on my side.

249
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:11,421
You're going down,

250
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:13,298
one way or another.

251
00:11:17,886 --> 00:11:20,722
That's the son of the
police commissioner for ya.

252
00:11:20,722 --> 00:11:24,642
The guy thinks
he can beat anybody.

253
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:25,643
Huh?

254
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:26,769
Maybe he's figured out

255
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:29,022
the secret to Rouga's
strategy somehow.

256
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:31,858
Can someone please
let me in on the secret?

257
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:33,776
♪

258
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:36,196
No way, you're kidding me,
Rouga's really who?

259
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:38,239
You're saying the guy's
a wanted criminal fighter

260
00:11:38,239 --> 00:11:40,491
‐on the run?
‐Shh!

261
00:11:40,491 --> 00:11:47,999
♪

262
00:11:47,999 --> 00:11:51,669
Shiden, Hayate,
attack the fighter!

263
00:11:51,669 --> 00:11:55,548
Destruct‐o slam!

264
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:57,926
Gale force of steel!

265
00:11:57,926 --> 00:12:00,303
♪

266
00:12:00,303 --> 00:12:02,555
Five Heavenly Swords Onimaru.

267
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:04,849
Twisted Spirit Purification!

268
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:09,520
Now I cast Bold Retaliation.

269
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,190
Time for a final phase.

270
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:16,319
I pay one gauge and set
Super Lethal Formation.

271
00:12:16,319 --> 00:12:18,404
Zanya doesn't waste any time.

272
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:20,114
There's his favorite move.

273
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:22,659
This game is officially on.

274
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:23,826
Set.

275
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:27,580
If we can just maintain
enough Life Points,

276
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,291
then Rouga will have no
choice but to use his Impact.

277
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:33,002
And when he does,
our pro will win.

278
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:35,588
♪

279
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:38,967
You're better than I
thought, Tsukikage's buddy.

280
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:40,218
The name's Zanya,

281
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:43,054
and it's about time
you started using it.

282
00:12:43,054 --> 00:12:44,722
Never!

283
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:47,433
You think that you can
tell me what to do?

284
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:50,603
You know nothing about me
or what I've gone through.

285
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:52,438
♪

286
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,732
Most kids did their best
to move away from the place

287
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:55,942
where I grew up.

288
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:57,610
A few of them became
trapped there,

289
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:59,862
living lives they never chose.

290
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:02,657
For us, learning people's
names was pointless.

291
00:13:02,657 --> 00:13:06,244
It didn't help to try and
remember who they once were.

292
00:13:06,244 --> 00:13:09,747
Can your precious justice
keep you warm at night?

293
00:13:09,747 --> 00:13:11,708
Or feed you when you're hungry?

294
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,918
Can it make you less lonely?

295
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:15,378
Well, maybe, uh‐‐

296
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:17,755
You wouldn't last
ten minutes where I'm from.

297
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:20,383
To survive, I had to acquire
an overwhelming power

298
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:23,094
that would destroy all
who stood in my way.

299
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:26,264
I lived by the code
might makes right.

300
00:13:26,264 --> 00:13:30,643
I call Armor Knight, Eagle,
to the left area!

301
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:32,145
We've got you now.

302
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:35,189
And I Buddy Call
Armor Knight, Cerberus Ace

303
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:38,192
to the right position.

304
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:40,611
With a Buddy Gift,
he regains one Life Point.

305
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:42,238
You're up, Ace.

306
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:48,327
♪

307
00:13:48,327 --> 00:13:50,621
Demonic Equip Combination.

308
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:53,666
Cerberus Ace has entered
the soul of Explosive Axe,

309
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,501
Ricdeau Demon Slay.

310
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:57,837
I got a bad feeling about this.

311
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:59,630
I call to the left.

312
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:01,090
Devour eagle!

313
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,301
Descend upon us!

314
00:14:03,301 --> 00:14:06,971
Why does this keep
happening to me?

315
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:09,807
The largest of the
Armorknight monsters,

316
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:12,143
Armorknight Bahamut!

317
00:14:12,143 --> 00:14:15,021
♪

318
00:14:15,021 --> 00:14:17,440
I always forget
how ginormous it is.

319
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,649
Well played, Rouga.

320
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:20,151
Nothing quite says
"intimidation"

321
00:14:20,151 --> 00:14:22,737
like calling a
massive Size 3 monster.

322
00:14:22,737 --> 00:14:24,155
It's huge!

323
00:14:24,155 --> 00:14:25,740
Size isn't the problem.

324
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:28,659
Its power and defense
are both 11,000.

325
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:29,911
Zanya's in trouble.

326
00:14:29,911 --> 00:14:31,204
Aside from being very strong,

327
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:35,666
Bahamut also restores four
life points to the fighter.

328
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:39,629
I move Accelerate Ninja,
Hayate to the center.

329
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:42,215
It's like that, huh?

330
00:14:42,215 --> 00:14:46,302
Take out Hayate with
Roaring Explosion Surge!

331
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:49,680
♪

332
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,681
Go with honor.

333
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:52,100
Thanks, Hayate.

334
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:56,521
‐I'm not done yet.
‐Huh?

335
00:14:56,521 --> 00:14:57,730
(yells)

336
00:14:57,730 --> 00:15:01,526
I cast Art of Body Replacement.

337
00:15:01,526 --> 00:15:04,779
Zanya not take any damage
this turn either, kem.

338
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:05,905
He still has 10 Life left,

339
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,407
‐and Rouga has 9.
‐It almost like they starting

340
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:10,368
from beginning again, kem.

341
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:14,705
I Buddy Call Nanomachine
Ninja, Tsukikage to the left.

342
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:16,374
Nin!

343
00:15:16,374 --> 00:15:17,375
Well done.

344
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,668
You keep evading my attacks

345
00:15:18,668 --> 00:15:20,962
and have managed to
maintain your Life Points.

346
00:15:20,962 --> 00:15:24,465
It's clear that you really
want to impress your father.

347
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:26,717
I'm not dedicating
my victory to my father.

348
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:28,719
This is all for somebody else.

349
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:30,388
Well, who is it?

350
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:33,141
He was a hero with
the most noble of goals.

351
00:15:33,141 --> 00:15:35,852
Someone I've looked up to
for most of my life.

352
00:15:35,852 --> 00:15:37,061
But now he's different.

353
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:39,105
He's not the guy
I thought he was,

354
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:40,857
like those kids he grew up with.

355
00:15:40,857 --> 00:15:43,860
He chose to walk
down the wrong path.

356
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:46,112
Huh?

357
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:48,906
Shiden, attack the fighter!

358
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:52,076
Destruct‐o slash!

359
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:54,245
Tsukikage, get him!

360
00:15:54,245 --> 00:15:55,830
Nin!

361
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:57,415
♪

362
00:15:57,415 --> 00:15:59,584
Fight, Heavenly Swords, Onimaru!

363
00:15:59,584 --> 00:16:02,962
Twisted Spirit Purification!

364
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,505
End of move.

365
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:06,090
I must say that when
this game started,

366
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:08,593
I thought Danger World
had the advantage.

367
00:16:08,593 --> 00:16:09,969
But all of a
sudden, here we are

368
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:12,305
with Zanya up 11 Life to three.

369
00:16:12,305 --> 00:16:14,182
(chuckling)

370
00:16:14,182 --> 00:16:16,142
It looks like that
loathsome Aragami's luck

371
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:17,977
is finally about to run out.

372
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:20,354
If Rouga has any hope
of wiping out all their

373
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:22,398
Life Points at once...

374
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,066
He'll have to use
an impact card.

375
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:26,527
And he'll fall right
into Big Z's trap,

376
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:29,947
exactly the way
you guys planned it.

377
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:31,449
I get it now.

378
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:33,784
But I'm a little unclear
on why you want to dedicate

379
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:35,536
your victory to him.

380
00:16:35,536 --> 00:16:38,289
I was raised to pursue
the ideals of justice,

381
00:16:38,289 --> 00:16:41,292
and I admired him because
he said he was the same.

382
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:42,668
But then he changed,

383
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:46,881
and now, I want him to
realize the mistake he's made.

384
00:16:46,881 --> 00:16:48,966
Does that answer your question?

385
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,593
Hm.

386
00:16:50,593 --> 00:16:53,137
Gao's the one who
gave me the idea.

387
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,222
Mikado?

388
00:16:54,222 --> 00:16:56,390
He showed me that in times
of struggle and confusion,

389
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,975
our friends need help.

390
00:16:57,975 --> 00:17:00,561
You know, to get them
on the right path,

391
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:02,021
to stand by them,

392
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:05,650
even when they've
made bad choices.

393
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:07,276
Stand by them.

394
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:13,699
♪

395
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:15,952
And I call to the left.

396
00:17:15,952 --> 00:17:18,287
Phalanx Dragon.

397
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:21,165
Hey.

398
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:23,459
You didn't pay any gauge
when you called that monster.

399
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:28,923
♪

400
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:30,049
That's it.

401
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,426
I'm not gonna
keep quiet anymore.

402
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:35,388
I cast Dimensional
Demon Slay Slash!

403
00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:36,889
Dimensional Demon Slay Slash

404
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:39,016
destroys one card from
the opponent's gauge

405
00:17:39,016 --> 00:17:42,061
while increasing the
user's gauge by one.

406
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:45,356
Attacks!

407
00:17:45,356 --> 00:17:48,734
Now you can't use your
Super Lethal Formation,

408
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:52,446
and my gauge shoots up to four.

409
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:53,864
It looks like your strategy

410
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:55,741
of keeping your gauge
at a bare minimum

411
00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:58,536
has worked against you.

412
00:17:58,536 --> 00:18:00,121
I didn't expect this.

413
00:18:00,121 --> 00:18:01,872
What can I do?

414
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:03,624
Is this the end?

415
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:07,920
Attack the fighter with
Roaring Explosion Surge!

416
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:10,214
I stopped questioning
what's good or bad

417
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:11,924
a long time ago.

418
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:14,385
♪

419
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:18,180
But now I know
what I have to do.

420
00:18:19,807 --> 00:18:21,475
(yelling)

421
00:18:21,475 --> 00:18:25,313
♪

422
00:18:25,313 --> 00:18:26,897
Final phase.

423
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:29,483
It's time I started
acting like a real friend

424
00:18:29,483 --> 00:18:31,110
instead of a coward.

425
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:34,822
I cast Ultimate Battle Skill.

426
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:38,117
MEGA Demon Slay!

427
00:18:38,117 --> 00:18:41,495
(yelling)

428
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:46,167
♪

429
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:47,293
Game over.

430
00:18:47,293 --> 00:18:49,629
Winner: Rouga Aragami.

431
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:51,422
(cheering)

432
00:18:51,422 --> 00:18:52,590
Can you say "surprise"?

433
00:18:52,590 --> 00:18:54,258
Rouga was down
by eight Life Points,

434
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:57,094
but he's turned the tables
in dramatic fashion.

435
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:59,764
This isn't happening, no one
can come back like that.

436
00:18:59,764 --> 00:19:00,848
What a nightmare.

437
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:03,434
Wait, that's it‐‐of course,
I must be dreaming.

438
00:19:03,434 --> 00:19:05,269
Okay, don't worry,
this is a bad dream.

439
00:19:05,269 --> 00:19:08,272
A dream, you hear,
this just can't be real!

440
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:09,482
With this victory,

441
00:19:09,482 --> 00:19:12,068
Team Purgatory draws even
with Team Balle du Soleil,

442
00:19:12,068 --> 00:19:13,152
which means that next up

443
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:16,864
is a one match to win
'em all ultimate showdown!

444
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:19,325
You couldn't script it
any better than this.

445
00:19:19,325 --> 00:19:20,368
Sorry, guys.

446
00:19:20,368 --> 00:19:22,995
I was so close, I just
didn't push hard enough.

447
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,541
It's up to you now.

448
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:30,294
Come on, you fought
a great game.

449
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:32,463
Hey, Mikado.

450
00:19:32,463 --> 00:19:34,840
You should be the one
to save Purgatory Knight.

451
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,467
That guy's made up his mind.

452
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:37,802
I don't agree.

453
00:19:37,802 --> 00:19:40,012
He needs a friend
to show him the way.

454
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:46,227
♪

455
00:19:46,227 --> 00:19:47,853
What's shakin', Rouga?

456
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:50,272
Out of my way,
Tetsuya Kurodake.

457
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:51,649
Uh...

458
00:19:51,649 --> 00:19:54,068
♪

459
00:19:54,068 --> 00:19:55,569
What's up with him, yo?

460
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:57,905
Why's he gotta be such a hater?

461
00:19:57,905 --> 00:19:58,823
Hm?

462
00:19:58,823 --> 00:20:02,660
You know, I think he
just said your name.

463
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:04,161
(gasps)

464
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:07,957
♪

465
00:20:07,957 --> 00:20:09,500
You mean to tell me
that young man

466
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:12,712
‐isn't Wolf anymore.
‐That's right.

467
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:13,963
Hm.

468
00:20:13,963 --> 00:20:16,882
I can understand your motives.

469
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:19,510
But he must make up for
the crimes he's committed,

470
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:20,803
don't you think?

471
00:20:20,803 --> 00:20:24,348
Sometimes, justice comes
in different forms, Father.

472
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:26,726
♪

473
00:20:26,726 --> 00:20:29,562
You learn fast,
you know‐‐just like me.

474
00:20:29,562 --> 00:20:31,689
♪

475
00:20:31,689 --> 00:20:34,191
(solo clapping)

476
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:37,903
You never cease to amaze me.

477
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:39,780
And now that you've
helped me as promised,

478
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:41,866
I'm sure we'll
remain good friends

479
00:20:41,866 --> 00:20:44,702
till the end of our lives.

480
00:20:45,870 --> 00:20:47,496
There's something I need to say.

481
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:48,706
Go ahead.

482
00:20:48,706 --> 00:20:51,292
Kyoya, what you're
doing is wrong.

483
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:54,879
You have to put a stop
to that plan of yours.

484
00:20:54,879 --> 00:20:56,672
(gasps)

485
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:57,882
When we were younger,

486
00:20:57,882 --> 00:21:00,760
I noticed a mistake that
you made during a Buddyfight.

487
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:03,846
I wasn't able to say
anything about it to you then,

488
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:06,557
but I'm calling you out now.

489
00:21:06,557 --> 00:21:08,225
I suppose you're
referring to that time

490
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:10,728
I had Dragonic
Charge in my hand.

491
00:21:10,728 --> 00:21:12,271
You knew?

492
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:15,024
♪

493
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:18,652
I've always wondered why you
didn't point out my mistake.

494
00:21:18,652 --> 00:21:22,281
Kyoya, don't tell me that you...

495
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:24,992
♪

496
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:25,993
Yes.

497
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:27,953
I did that on purpose.

498
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:31,165
I did it to test you.

499
00:21:31,165 --> 00:21:32,708
Why would you do that?

500
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:35,127
You're no longer the
friend I once knew.

501
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:38,339
‐How very unfortunate.
‐Wait, let me explain.

502
00:21:38,339 --> 00:21:41,091
‐I thought that if‐‐oof!
‐Wait.

503
00:21:41,091 --> 00:21:43,302
There's no need
to erase his memories.

504
00:21:43,302 --> 00:21:46,055
Master Kyoya is right,
there's nothing he can do.

505
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:48,599
All of our preparations
have been completed.

506
00:21:48,599 --> 00:21:50,726
Even if our plan gets
leaked at this point,

507
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:52,770
it won't make any difference.

508
00:21:52,770 --> 00:21:54,188
Too bad.

509
00:21:54,188 --> 00:22:00,110
♪

510
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:02,947
Your memories will be
my parting gift to you.

511
00:22:02,947 --> 00:22:05,115
Wh‐‐what are you saying?

512
00:22:05,115 --> 00:22:07,326
When this tournament is over,

513
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:09,620
I don't ever want
to see you again.

514
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:10,871
(gasps)

515
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:13,123
Don't ever call
or try to visit.

516
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:15,084
If I so much as see
your pathetic face

517
00:22:15,084 --> 00:22:16,460
within 20 feet of me,

518
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:19,171
I'll take more
than your memories.

519
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:20,339
Agh, wait!

520
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:23,133
You said you were my friend,
was that just a lie?

521
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,553
I don't understand,
I did everything you asked.

522
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:26,971
How can you do this to me?

523
00:22:26,971 --> 00:22:30,599
After all this time,
am I worth nothing to you?

524
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:34,270
Nice knowing you... my friend.

525
00:22:34,270 --> 00:22:46,282
♪

526
00:22:49,159 --> 00:22:51,495
‐It's time for...
‐Tasuku and Gao's...

